Visual Suggestions 6

Suggestions:

Addressing the issue of flight delays requires effective planning and collaboration between the governing agencies, airport officials, and the airlines themselves. The following suggestion are steps that can reduce flight delays.
  1. Airlines to schedule flights that can be effectively supported by their fleet, although this would mean reduced flights and profits.
  2. Better airport design considerations when expanding an airport which includes runway orientations with respect to topography and wind directions.
  3. Improve air traffic control systems to allow for more intensive usage of existing capacity (by shortening the distance between aircraft in airspace).
  4. Improve the services of airport governing bodies such as airport security by having effective security checks and better information materials for the passengers.
